{
  "stem": "268.5",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Something that looked like coffee.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "It was like some kind of an ersatz.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And you got a slice of bread.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Not a real heavy slice.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "A medium slice of bread.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And sometimes on weekends, you would get a spoonful of marmalade or Jell-O or a little square of margarine spread.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "So it was in the morning.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "At noon, it was, again, a soup.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "Maybe if you're lucky, you found a potato or two swimming in it.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And that soup-- again, this was not a dining-room arrangement.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "You carried your little dish with you.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "It was like an aluminum bowl-- a bowl.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And you carried them on your belt.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "This was-- that and a spoon.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "It was neatly shined.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "You carried that on your belt.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "And this was your equipment.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "Without it, you were never moved anyplace.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "And so you, again, got a slice of bread.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "And depending how big a bread, how many people, sometimes the bread-- the rations were smaller, sometimes bigger.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "Sometimes they'll slice a bread-- let's say a pound-and-a-half of bread maybe at noon maybe in 10 or 12 slices.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "In the evening, it would be maybe eight slices, so the slices were thicker.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "But that was your ration.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "In calories, it was estimated-- I didn't know then, but as I found out reading after the war, it was designed somewhere between 600 and 700 calories a day, which is not a whole lot to exist on.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "And in the evening, again, a slice of bread.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "Sometimes they would have like some kind of a slice of salami.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "But usually, it was a spoonful of marmalade or, as I said, Jell-O.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "And some bitter, dark liquid that looks like-- looked like coffee, but it didn't taste or smell like.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "That was it.",
      "word_count": 3
    }
  ],
